node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter managed millions of dollars in investor money for nearly a decade and one of the funds ran with ~$30MM in assets averaged a 13% return for 7 years And let me tell you, there are some important lessons that learned.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter managed millions of dollars in investor money for nearly a decade and one of the funds ran with ~$30MM in assets averaged a 13% return for 7 years And let me tell you, there are some important lessons that learned.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 1.Risk is fine in moderation. It's alright to make some risky investments here and there, but it shouldn't be a high % of your portfolio. 20% of my portfolio is dedicated to higher-risk investments.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve och-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 2. The best deals are private. Even though there are tons of great options to invest in with the open stock market investing in private deals gives you access to more 10x and 100x opportunities.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 3. Big gains are nice, but consistent gains are key. Even though winningit oig on some call options will give me you a nice screenshot, what really matters is your compound annual growth rate over 10, 20, or 30 years. don't like options.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '-DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 4. Day trading is bad. This should be self-explanatory, but if Warren Buffet, the greatest investor of all time isn't making any trades, neither am I.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 5. Most people are better with ETF's. When it comes down to picking individual stocks, most people (even hedge funds) will not outperform basic EFTs like vOO and SPY over 30 years. If you you can't beat them, join them.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter Now that I'm no longer managing other people's money, I'm your local financial meme dealer. make content that is both educating and entertaining while writing some newsletters every week. The best part? The content and one of my newsletters are free if you follow me.'.

node.text:
This is how the wealthy continue to build and maintain wealth.

Instead of spending their main income directly on big expenses such as a wedding or a big vacation they invest it in an income producing asset first.

This gives them more freedom to make more money over time and have a bigger wedding/ more vacations 

Credit to: marktilbury on TikTok
Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
@realbusinessowners have both built multiple businesses to 7 and 8-figures starting from absolutely nothing. They're now here to give you guys the No-BS tactics and tips that they've learned along the way. 🔥🔥
Follow @realbusinessowners for more. 🔥🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners Here are 10 lessons we learned being in business over the past 13 years...'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 1. Most progress will be made during difficult times 2. You will get screwed over, it's apart of the game.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 3. Entrepreneurship is self development disguised as business. 4. Making money is easy, keeping it is the hard part.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 5. You'll never be satisfied by the end result, enjoy the journey. 6. Building a business isn't that glamorous, just a ton of work.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 7. Once you can afforo afford the Lambo, it isn't that cool. 8. Uncertainty is the barrier of entry to success.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 9. Always focus on solutions, never the problem. 10. Discipline will take you further than motivation ever will.'.

The harder your money works, the less taxes you'll pay. This is one of the main reason how Warren Buffett's tax rate is 17 while the average American's rate is 24%'.

node.text:
When your money is working for you you are getting paid in capital gains, dividends, etc...

This is how the rich make money. When you do this your tax rate is far lower because investments and assets are taxed at a lower rate than wages.

This means the average American pays a higher percent of taxes than the average millionaire. This is why we always stress to get money and buy assets!

Follow us @businessequity
